#1 Recurrent rectal cancer with extensive presacral tissue involvement
Abdominal perineal resection, presacral tumor excision, possible full or partial cystectomy, and pelvic reconstruction is planned for October 29, 2010.
It was made known to the patient that if the procedure ended up being too extensive, there is the possibility that all parties may need to abort.
For the time-being, he will be on CRS enhanced recovery protocol.  Intraoperative findings may need this adjusted.

[end section id="20112"]

