Indication: pain.
Prochlorperazine [COMPAZINE] 10-mg tablet 1 TABLET by mouth every 6 hours as-needed.
Indication: nausea and vomiting.
Triamcinolone Acetonide [KENALOG] 0.025 % ointment 1 apply topically as directed by prescriber.
Site: Affected area.
Indication: peeling skin.
Instructions: Use twice-daily for 10-14 days when red and peeling then stop for several days. Repeat as-needed.  Avoid continuous use longer than 2 weeks.
Tylenol Extra-Strength 500-mg tablet 1-2 tablets by mouth as-needed.
Indication: As-needed.
These are the patient's medications as of Friday, October 29, 2010 at 10:20 AM.

